# Square up to the washing machine (wall_aligner.py): rotate in place until the
# base +x axis is perpendicular to the NEAREST straight segment the lidar sees
# in front — the machine's front panel, a bounded line whose two endpoints are
# visible in the scan. Nothing is locked in odom: the segment is re-fitted from
# the live scan every control cycle, and the result is verified with a
# stationary multi-scan fit before reporting success.
#
# Calibration trick for CloseToWall: park the robot at the PERFECT final depth,
# call this (it barely moves if already square) and read `distance` — that
# number is the `distance` to request from CloseToWall.
float32 max_range   # m; > 0 overrides the node's max_detect_range for the segment search
bool center         # also strafe so the segment midpoint sits on the base centerline
---
bool success
string error
float32 distance        # verified perpendicular base_link -> face distance (m), minus front_offset
float32 yaw_error       # residual yaw error at finish (rad)
float32 segment_length  # detected face width (m) — sanity-check it matches the machine
